  "description": "Change of use from single dwelling (use class C3) to House in Multiple Occupation (Use class C4).",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "The application would, due to the housing typology of the existing building, materially change the character of the subject property and the surrounding environment through an increased intensification of use over and above what could be considered acceptable, resulting in detrimental impact on the residential amenity of nearby occupiers and would fail to comply with the criteria set out in policies DC4, DC5 and DC61 of the Havering Core Strategy Development Control Policies and Development Control Document DPD 2008.",
    "The application would provide cramped, inadequately-sized and sub-standard accommodation for future occupants, and would be unacceptable when assessed against the National Planning Policy Framework 2019 [as amended], policies D3, D4 and D6 of the London Plan, policies CP17, DC2, DC4, DC5 and DC61 of the Havering Core Strategy and Development Control Policies DPD 2008, and the Residential Design SPD.",
    "Statement Required by Article 35 (2) of the Town and Country Planning (Development Management Procedure) (England) Order 2015: Consideration was given to seeking amendments, but given conflict with adopted planning policy, and principle objections to the scheme, it was considered expedient to issue a decision in line with the expectations under paragraph 47 of the National Planning Policy Framework 2019 [as amended]."
